headline: Body of Florida woman found in septic tank, handyman charged with murder
author: Natalie O'Neill
sentences:
I’ve never seen anything like it,”
Comments:
Maybe not this exact scenario, Mr. Sheriff, but crimes that share key elements with this one are exceedingly common if you're paying even the least bit of attention.

Keoki Hilo Demich, 34, was charged with murdering Cynthia Cole, 57, who went missing shortly after attending an art festival in Jensen Beach over a week ago, Martin County Sheriff said on Facebook Saturday.
Cops allegedly found doorbell camera footage of Demich leaving Cole’s Jeep near her home the night she was last seen and arrested him on Friday, according to WPBF News.
The body of a missing Florida woman was found in a septic tank behind her home after she was allegedly killed and dumped there by her handyman, according to police.
